description
-----------
| 

hg related information

| 

  only works on hg version of the bot 

| 

commands
--------
| 

1) *hg-annotate (hg-blame)*

    :description: annotate the changes of a file

    :permissions: USER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !hg-annotate gozerbot/bot.py
        <output> file not found


2) *hg-changes*

    :description: show changes in the current release (tip) or between two releases

    :permissions: USER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !hg-changes tip
        <output> tip - tip: mod doc/baseplugs/ALIAS, mod doc/baseplugs/ALL,
        <output>  mod doc/baseplugs/AT, mod doc/baseplugs/CHANPERM,
        <output>  mod doc/baseplugs/CHOICE, mod doc/baseplugs/CODE,
        <output>  mod doc/baseplugs/CORE, mod doc/baseplugs/COUNT, mod
        <output>  doc/baseplugs/FLEET, mod doc/baseplugs/GOOGLETALK,
        <output>  mod doc/baseplugs/GREP, mod doc/baseplugs/IGNORE,
        <output>  mod doc/baseplugs/INSTALL, mod doc/baseplugs/IRC,
        <output>  mod doc/baseplugs/JABBER, mod doc/baseplugs/JOB, mod
        <output>  doc/baseplugs/MISC, mod doc/baseplugs/NICKCAPTURE,
        <output>  mod doc/baseplugs/NICKSERV, mod doc/baseplugs/NOT,
         - output trunked -



    ::

        <user> !hg-changes 1900 tip
        <output> 1900 - tip: mod .hgtags, mod README, mod bin/gozerbot,
        <output>  add bin/gozerbot-init, mod bin/gozerbot-start, add
        <output>  bin/gozerbot-udp, add bin/gozerbot-upgrade, mod ev/null,
        <output>  mod ev/null, mod ev/null, mod ev/null, mod doc/FAQ,
        <output>  mod ev/null, mod ev/null, mod ev/null, mod ev/null,
        <output>  mod ev/null, mod ev/null, mod ev/null, mod ev/null,
        <output>  mod ev/null, mod doc/THNX, mod ev/null, mod ev/null,
        <output>  mod ev/null, mod ev/null, mod ev/null, add doc/baseplugs/ALIAS,
        <output>  add doc/baseplugs/ALL, add doc/baseplugs/AT, add doc/baseplugs/CHANPERM,
        <output>  add doc/baseplugs/CHOICE, add doc/baseplugs/CODE,
         - output trunked -


3) *hg-committers (committers)*

    :description: shows hg committer statistics

    :permissions: USER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !hg-committers
        <output> top committers: bart@dunker.lan: 728, bart@bart-desktop:
        <output>  671, bart@localhost.my.domain: 440, dunker@dunker-done:
        <output>  263, dunker@laptop: 238, bart@dunker: 104, bart@82-217-121-99.telephony.multikabel.net:
        <output>  58, wijnand@freecode.nl: 54, Bart Thate <bart@r8.cg.nu>:
        <output>  44, sqrbass@localhost.nl.eu.org: 26, sqrbass@complex.shrine.net:
        <output>  17, bart@desktop: 16, Antoine Beaupr√© <anarcat@koumbit.org>:
        <output>  15, sqrbass@bus.idca.nl: 8, sqrbass@ryoko: 6, dunker@bart-laptop:
        <output>  6, wildrover@rubik.cluenet.org: 5, sqrbass@r8.cg.nu:
        <output>  3, bart@gozer.bot: 3, sqrbass@localhost: 2, bart@pyjbot.cg.nu:
        <output>  2, Bart Thae  <bart@r8.cg.nu>: 2, wijnand@dasbier.spoofed.nl:
         - output trunked -


4) *hg-log*

    :description: show the changelog for the repo, or for a file

    :permissions: USER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !hg-log gozerplugs/plugs/core.py
        <output> file not found


